 Trojan War. By thoroughly mastering and inspiringly refashioning a vast amount of literary material, Ovid generates a systematic reconstruction of the archetypal hero, Achilles. Thus, he projects himself as a worthy successor of Homer in the epic tradition, a master epicist, and a par to his great Latin predecessor, Vergil.  aIssued also in print.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 28. Feb 2023) 0aEpic poetry, GreekxHistory and criticism. 0aEpic poetry, LatinxHistory and criticism. 0aLatein /Literatur, Literaturgeschichte. 0aOvid. 0aTrojan WarxLiterature and the war. 4aLatein /Literatur, Literaturgeschichte. 4aOvid. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / Ancient & Classical.2bisacsh  aLatin Epic.  aOvid.08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Classics and Near East Studies 2000-2014 (EN)z978311062109908iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1z978311023857008iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertDGBA Classics and Near East Studies 2000 - 2014z9783110636178oZDB-23-GCN08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK GESAMTPAKET / COMPLETE PACKAGE 2008z9783110212129oZDB-23-DGG08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2008z978311021213608iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertE-BOOK PAKET ALTERTUM 2008z9783110209075oZDB-23-DGD0 cprintz978311020048540uhttps://doi.org/10.1515/978311020430840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9783110204308423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9783110204308/original  a978-3-11-021213-6  E-BOOK PACKAGE ENGLISH LANGUAGES TITLES 2008b2008  a978-3-11-023857-0  DGBA Backlist Complete English Language 2000-2014 PART1c2000d2014  a978-3-11-062109-9  DGBA Backlist Classics and Near East Studies 2000-2014 (EN)c200